{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2012}} '''Graeme Bennett''' (born 7 May 1965 in [[Inverness]]) is a former [[Scotland|Scottish]] [[football (soccer)|football]] [[midfielder]]. Now retired, he held the position of [[Director of football]] at [[Inverness Caledonian Thistle F.C.]]. He is nicknamed 'Grassa'.<ref>[http://www.zoominfo.com/people/Bennett_Graeme_55148873.aspx Details] from [[ZoomInfo]]</ref>
As a player the combative Bennett made his [[Scottish Football League]] debut for the newly created Inverness club in their [[1994-95 in Scottish football|first season]] in existence.<ref name=Bennett>[http://findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_qn4156/is_20061105/ai_n16826146 Article on Bennett]</ref> He eventually left the club to become player-manager of [[Clachnacuddin F.C.]] and concentrate on his [[double glazing]] firm but soon returned in the director's role.<ref name=Bennett/> Although overseeing a fairly regular turnover of men in the managerial role, Bennett has been constant in the director's role since the days of [[Steve Paterson]].<ref name=Bennett/>
Bennett also held the position of vice-chairman of the club.<ref>[http://www.dailyrecord.co.uk/sport/football-news/scottish-football/spl-football/inverness-caley-fc/2008/04/11/alan-savage-quits-as-inverness-chairman-86908-20379612/ Alan Savage quits as Inverness chairman]</ref> Following the club's relegation in 2009 his director of football role became unsalaried as the club made a series a cost-cutting measures.<ref>[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/i/inverness_ct/8111762.stm Inverness cuts 'warning to SPL' ]</ref>
