'''ISFnet Inc.''' (株式会社アイエスエフネット) is a multinational integrated IT services company based in [[Tokyo]], [[Japan]]. The company was founded in January 2000 <ref name="ACCJ">American Chamber of Commerce Japan Journal July 2006 "Upsetting the Status Quo: From Service to Customer Serving" http://www.accj.or.jp/doclib/journal/15_ss_it_july06.pdf</ref> by Japanese [[entrepreneur]], [[Yukiyoshi Watanabe]] (渡邉 幸義). It currently operates in 16 locations <ref name="ISFnet">ISFnet Company Profile http://www.isfnet.co.jp/company/office.html</ref> across Japan and has subsidiaries in [[China]], [[Korea]] and [[Singapore]].
==ISFnet Harmony Ltd.== ISFnet Harmony Ltd. is a wholly owned [[subsidiary]] of ISFnet Inc, designated as a ''special'' subsidiary under the [[Japanese Disability Employment Encouragement Law]]. Set up in 2008, ISFnet Harmony Ltd. offers employment opportunities in the IT sector to people wifjgukhibjmhklj;lmnzdatrth disabilities.<ref name="ZDnet">ZDnet Japan, April 18th 2008, "Company Stories: ISFnet Harmony", http://japan.zdnet.com/company/story/0,3200081168,20170610,00.htm</ref>
==ISFnet Care Ltd.== ISFnet Care Ltd. was established to offer diverse employment opportunities to groups of people who often find themselves excluded from the mainstream labor force, such as primary caregivers, people with disabilities or mental health problems.<ref name="ISFnet"/>
==Hospitality In IT== ISFnet Inc. has pioneered ''[[hospitality]]'' in the IT services sector (the adoption of 5-star hotel service standards), and was the focus of a book, ''IT Business Strategy and Corporate Hospitality'' <ref name="Book">Masamitsu Hayashida, 2010, "IT Business Strategy and Corporate Hospitality", Diamond Inc., Tokyo</ref> by Japanese business guru [[Masamitsu Hayashida]].,<ref name="ISFnet"/><ref name="Hayashida Institute">Hayashida Institute, http://www.hayashida-cs.co.jp/profile.html</ref>
==Domestic Offices== [[Sapporo]], [[Sendai]], [[Utsunomiya]], [[Numazu]], [[Shizuoka, Shizuoka|Shizuoka]], [[Nagoya]], [[Osaka]], [[Hiroshima]], [[Fukuoka]], [[Tokyo]], [[Morioka]].
