{{multiple issues| {{Notability|Org|date=March 2011}} {{primary sources|date=March 2011}} }}
{{Infobox organisation | name = Independent Certified Practising Accountants | image = | established = {{flagicon|UK}} England, UK, {{Start date|2001}} | type = Professional association | services = [[Accountancy]] | headquarters = Imperial House, 1a Standen Avenue, Hornchurch, Essex, RM12 6AA | region_served = UK | website = [http://www.icpa.org.uk icpa.org.uk] | footnotes = }}
The '''Institute of Certified Practising Accountants''' ('''ICPA''') was founded in 2001 in the [[United Kingdom]]. It is a professional organisation representing practising accountants.
The Association's headquarters are in [[Hornchurch]], [[England]].
Although this association uses the word "[[Institute]]", this term is a protected word in the United Kingdom,<ref>[http://www.companieshouse.gov.uk/about/gbhtml/gbf2.shtml#three 'Sensitive words' FAQ on Companies House website]</ref> and use of the title "institute" requires approval from the [[Secretary of State]]; failure to seek approval is a [[criminal offence]].<ref>[http://www.companieshouse.gov.uk/about/gbhtml/gbf3.shtml#one 'Business Names - GBF3, guidance on Companies House website] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080913085135/http://www.companieshouse.gov.uk/about/gbhtml/gbf3.shtml |date=2008-09-13 }}</ref> It is not clear whether the ICPA has obtained such approval.
== Designation ==
The ICPA offers its members the designation of Certified Practising Accountant (ICPA). Fellowship status is offered to members after an extra period of appropriate experience in professional practice.
== Membership requirements ==
The ICPA is open to practising Accountants whether members of a CCAB body or qualified by experience.
