{{Orphan|date=July 2016}}

'''Jacobus Enschedé I''' (19 March 1753 in [[Haarlem]] &ndash;1 January 1783 in Haarlem) was a Haarlem newspaper editor and printer.

==Biography==
He was a son of [[Johannes Enschedé (1708-1780)|Johannes Enschedé]] and [[Helena Hoefnagel]]. For some time he was a partner in the [[Joh. Enschedé|family company]]. On 7 September 1779 in [[Haarlem]] he married Gertruida Elisabeth van Oosten de Bruyn (Haarlem, 6 June 1759 &ndash;Velsen, 24 October 1810) the daughter of Mr. Gerrit Willem van Oosten de Bruyn and Maria Croon. He had no descendants in the company.

