{{Infobox Union |name= SARTUC |country= |affiliation= |members= |full_name= South Asian Regional Trade Union Council |native_name= |image= |founded= 1988 |current= |head= |dissolved_date= |dissolved_state= |merged_into= |office= |people= |website= |footnotes= }} <!-- Include all unused fields for future use. See [[template talk:Infobox Union]] for usage. --> The '''South Asian Regional Trade Union Council (SARTUC)''' is a [[federation]] of [[national trade union center]]s whose geographic scope covers South Asia. SARTUC's mission is to promote workers' rights within its member nations.<ref>[http://www.gurn.info/topic/trade/icftu_0604.pdf International Confederation of Free Trade Unions. ''The Spread of Bilateral and Regional Trade Agreements.'' June 2004.] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20061208160035/http://www.gurn.info/topic/trade/icftu_0604.pdf |date=2006-12-08 }}</ref>
